WITH data_string AS(
  SELECT "$facebook_main_query" AS data
), split_rows AS (
  SELECT TRIM(REPLACE(part, "(", ""), ")") AS row_text
  FROM data_string,
  UNNEST(SPLIT(data, " -ni- ")) AS part
), parsed_rows AS (
  SELECT
    SPLIT(row_text, "|")[OFFSET(0)] AS profile,
    CAST(SPLIT(row_text, "|")[OFFSET(1)] AS FLOAT64) AS metric1,
    CAST(SPLIT(row_text, "|")[OFFSET(2)] AS FLOAT64) AS metric2,
    CAST(SPLIT(row_text, "|")[OFFSET(3)] AS FLOAT64) AS metric3,
    CAST(SPLIT(row_text, "|")[OFFSET(4)] AS FLOAT64) AS metric4
  FROM split_rows
)
SELECT DISTINCT PERCENTILE_CONT(metric1, 0.75) OVER () AS Q3 FROM(
  SELECT
  metric1, 
  CASE
      WHEN metric1 < PERCENTILE_CONT(metric1, 0.25) OVER() THEN 'Low-Performer'
      WHEN metric1 >= PERCENTILE_CONT(metric1, 0.25) OVER() AND metric1 < PERCENTILE_CONT(metric1, 0.5) OVER() THEN 'Medium-Performer 1'
      WHEN metric1 >= PERCENTILE_CONT(metric1, 0.5) OVER() AND metric1 < PERCENTILE_CONT(metric1, 0.75) OVER() THEN 'Medium-Performer 2'
      WHEN metric1 >= PERCENTILE_CONT(metric1, 0.75) OVER() THEN 'Top-Performer'
  END AS category 
  FROM parsed_rows
)
WHERE CASE "$FILTER" 
WHEN "Alle" THEN TRUE
ELSE CONTAINS_SUBSTR(category, "$FILTER") END

WITH nutzer AS (
  SELECT
CASE
    WHEN CONTAINS_SUBSTR("${__user.login}", "dev") THEN "dev"
    WHEN CONTAINS_SUBSTR("${__user.login}", "mefo") THEN "mefo"
    WHEN CONTAINS_SUBSTR("${__user.email}", "@") THEN
      REGEXP_EXTRACT("${__user.email}", r'@([^\.]+)')  -- Extracts part after '@' and before the first '.' Example: ad.westphal@ndr.de => ndr
    WHEN NOT CONTAINS_SUBSTR("${__user.email}", "@")
         AND (CONTAINS_SUBSTR("${__user.email}", "viewer") 
         OR CONTAINS_SUBSTR("${__user.email}", "podcast")) THEN
            REGEXP_EXTRACT("${__user.email}", r'^([^-\s]+)')  -- Extracts part before the first '-'. Example: ndr-viewer => ndr
    ELSE
      "Anonym"
  END AS nutzer_lra
),
